<chapter xml:id="functions-testing"
         xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Functions and Testing</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>So far, we've written programs that have only used one function, named <c>main</c>. In this
      chapter, we will look at how to use multiple functions in a program to break up the code into
      smaller, more manageable pieces. We'll start by looking at some of the functions provided for
      us in the <c>math</c> library. Then, we'll learn how to define our own functions. Finally, we'll
      discuss strategies for incrementally developing and testing your code. </p>
  </introduction>

